112
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:52,130
Yes, he vanished without a trace.

113
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:56,920
When did this happen? When did Lee Kang San disappear?

114
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:02,030
You met Yook Dong Joo's father?

115
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:03,640
Yes.

116
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:05,350
I remember him.

117
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:07,870
That's impossible.

118
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,540
   

119
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:20,280
He passed away long before you were born. 
    

120
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,890
But I remembered meeting him.

121
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:25,810
There must be an error in your memories.

122
00:10:25,810 --> 00:10:28,100
He's the one who gave me the bag.

123
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,670
- He gave me the bag. 
 - What bag?

124
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:33,260
The bag I had when I got hit by the car.

125
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:35,440
You had a bag with you?

126
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,090
Yes.

127
00:10:38,290 --> 00:10:41,380
 Did the victim not have any belongings? 

128
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:43,240
 No. 

129
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:46,450
Where is your bag right now?

130
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:49,770
Didn't you have anything in it that we can use to identify you with?

131
00:10:49,770 --> 00:10:53,200
- He said there wasn't. 
 - You didn't check it yourself?

132
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,760
Hyung lost it.

133
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:57,540
- He lost it? 
 - Yes.

134
00:10:57,540 --> 00:11:00,420
But you're sure you had a bag with you?

135
00:11:00,420 --> 00:11:03,680
I'm sure. This man gave me the bag.

136
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:07,410
Meeting someone who passed away is impossible.

137
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:09,710
That's true, but...

138
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:13,570
It could be some sort of PTSD.

139
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:19,740
More importantly, tell me honestly what happened here.

140
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:25,400
I'm not sure what the truth is.

141
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:30,070
Does truth even exist?

142
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,920
What do you mean?

143
00:11:33,550 --> 00:11:38,980
If you don't believe it... even the truth isn't true anymore.

144
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:13,470
 It was torn down and moved to a new location... 

145
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:20,390
but he lived with his brother at a church-run facility called Cheonyoung Orphanage.

146
00:12:21,820 --> 00:12:27,360
They say misfortune comes in pairs, but how could both brothers go missing at once?

