245
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:18,810
Gosh, gosh. I-I'm sorry.

246
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:21,070
Something odd?

247
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:25,520
Yes, a trait that can be used to identify Lee Kang San.

248
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:32,740
By chance... did you find Kang San's corpse or something?

249
00:19:32,740 --> 00:19:36,240
G-Gosh, i-it's not like that. It's just research for my novel.

250
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:39,090
- Cut the crap and tell me the truth. 
 - It's really the truth!

251
00:19:39,090 --> 00:19:42,330
Why would I lie to you, Senior?

252
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:44,440
Because it's weird.

253
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:48,820
Earlier today, a detective came out of nowhere to look into Kang San's student record.

254
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:52,960
And now... you're asking about Kang San as well.

255
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:55,430
A d-detective?

256
00:19:55,430 --> 00:19:57,540
Was it a female detective?

257
00:19:58,340 --> 00:20:00,400
No.

258
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,580
   

259
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:04,080
You remember this student, right?

260
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:08,020
Is he someone I need to remember?

261
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:09,900
Twenty-seven years ago...

262
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:13,150
he came to me saying he had something to say about the Lake Sopyeong incident.

263
