 The murder case that took place at Lake Sopyeong. 

264
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:19,000
 To whom should I speak? 

265
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,320
 Do you know something? Huh? 

266
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,710
 Hold on. 

267
00:20:26,710 --> 00:20:28,730
 Hyungnim! 

268
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:31,430
 And I left him in your care. 

269
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:34,180
Did you?

270
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:37,910
What did this student tell you, Hyungnim?

271
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:43,560
 Is everything you told me the truth? 

272
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,500
 It's the truth. 

273
00:20:48,430 --> 00:20:53,350
 Did you... tell anyone else about this, by chance? 

274
00:20:53,350 --> 00:20:54,940
 No. 

275
00:20:55,710 --> 00:20:57,670
 Good. 

276
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:04,210
 I'm sure you know, but the people we have to fight aren't regular folks. 

277
00:21:04,210 --> 00:21:07,460
 You and I could both end up dead as well. 

278
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:09,560
 I'm aware of that. 

279
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:15,200
 By the way... your testimony alone isn't enough to prove it. 

280
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,650
 I-I have proof. 

281
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:20,440
 - Proof? 
 - Yes. 

282
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:23,810
 There's a videotape. 

283
00:21:23,810 --> 00:21:29,200
I have no recollection, so it must've been some useless talk.

284
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:36,030
By the way... as you did last time,

285
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:39,450
why do you keep digging up a case that's been over with for ages?

286
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:45,320
Because it doesn't look like it's over.

287
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:51,490
He didn't tell you why he was looking for Lee Kang San?

288
00:21:51,490 --> 00:21:53,730
It wasn't Kang San.

289
00:21:54,510 --> 00:21:56,890
He was looking for Kang San's brother.

290
00:21:56,890 --> 00:21:58,060
His brother?

291
00:21:58,060 --> 00:21:59,580
Yes.

292
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:03,730
I think he found out Kang San went missing when he came here.

293
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:12,370
Kang San has a scar on his back.

294
00:22:14,310 --> 00:22:17,310
I happened to see it, so I pretended not to have seen it.

295
00:22:20,230 --> 00:22:22,950
 It looked like a scar from getting beaten. 

296
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,990
If you happen to find Kang San, let me know.

297
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,640
I must tell him something.

298
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,910
Please hit me just once.

299
00:22:34,350 --> 00:22:38,260
Hit me just once, Senior. I'm not sure if this is a dream or reality—

300
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:39,810
Ouch.

301
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:43,420
It's indeed reality.

302
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:44,990
Take care.

303
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:46,950
What's hisname?

304
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:53,360
What's Lee Kang San's older brother's name?

305
00:22:54,150 --> 00:22:55,880
Ha Neul. 
  (Haneul means sky in Korean) 

306
00:22:56,550 --> 00:22:58,020
Sorry?

307
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:01,710
Sky.

308
00:23:02,370 --> 00:23:04,120
Lee Ha Neul.

309
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:13,010
Lee Ha Neul?

310
00:23:20,020 --> 00:23:21,760
Dong Joo!

311
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:27,170
Hey, did you meet the principal?

312
00:23:29,670 --> 00:23:31,190
Yeah...

313
00:23:37,310 --> 00:23:39,210
Is something wrong?

314
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:42,390
What's the matter?

315
00:23:43,170 --> 00:23:45,190
I wrote a novel.

316
00:23:45,190 --> 00:23:46,190
What?

317
00:23:46,190 --> 00:23:50,060
On a day when there's rain with thunder and lightning...

318
00:23:50,060 --> 00:23:52,440
a hole in spacetime was created like a blackhole,

319
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:56,100
which allowed the protagonist to travel through time to the future.

320
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:58,990
- Is it your next work? 
 - Hear me out.

321
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:01,530
 Ouch! 

322
00:24:02,710 --> 00:24:05,710
 But as soon as he arrived, he got hit by a car. 

323
00:24:05,710 --> 00:24:09,140
 Because he appeared out of nowhere as if he was pulled out of thin air. 

324
00:24:09,140 --> 00:24:11,780
He can't even call the ambulance because his phone's all broken.

325
00:24:11,780 --> 00:24:13,700
That's why I— No, no, no!

326
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:17,370
The driver of the car takes him to the hospital.

327
00:24:20,180 --> 00:24:21,550
But they said he died.

328
00:24:21,550 --> 00:24:24,850
 The patient has passed away. 

329
00:24:24,850 --> 00:24:27,400
He was announced dead.

330
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:32,130
But he came back to life, opening his eyes like a miracle.

331
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:35,470
He came back but couldn't remember anything, including his name.

332
00:24:35,470 --> 00:24:40,920
But he has a superpower that lets him hear people's suffering and teleports from anywhere, too.

333
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,810
Don't write about this.

334
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:44,900
Right? T-This is nonsense, right?

335
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:49,180
I mean, it's not nonsense for an SF novel. But it's bland.

336
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:52,490
I-It's bland?

337
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:55,590
It's so shocking for me!

338
00:24:56,630 --> 00:25:01,420
Hey, Yong Dae... in fact, I used...

339
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:05,090
- a novel written by a serial killer— 
 - Whoa!

340
00:25:05,090 --> 00:25:06,590
Yes, that's it.

341
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:09,170
Put serial murder in it!

342
00:25:09,170 --> 00:25:11,540
I can tell this one will be a big hit!

343
00:25:11,540 --> 00:25:13,320
G-Go write it out first.

344
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,670
Thanks.

345
00:25:15,670 --> 00:25:17,960
Man, don't mention it.

346
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:22,290
I can breathe now that I've told someone.

347
00:25:22,290 --> 00:25:23,870
Hey, I need to go.

348
00:25:23,870 --> 00:25:25,550
Laters!

349
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:31,660
Yes, Chief. Yes, I'm on my way. Yes.

350
00:25:40,190 --> 00:25:42,790
Lee Ha Neul...

351
00:25:46,940 --> 00:25:50,390
Sky... Sky...

352
00:25:52,830 --> 00:25:54,540
Kai?

353
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,970
Sky.

354
00:25:58,250 --> 00:25:59,990
Kai.

355
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:22,370
Are his treatments over?

356
00:26:22,370 --> 00:26:25,120
- I went to see him just now and— 
 - Detective Park!

357
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:27,500
...he seemed unstable for some reason.

358
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:32,080
Oh, it's probably because his memories aren't completely restored yet.

359
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:35,960
Yes, you don't need to worry about it.

360
00:26:38,610 --> 00:26:40,390
Hello.

361
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,400
How are you feeling?

362
00:26:44,610 --> 00:26:49,100
I have no difficulty doing daily tasks... for now.

363
00:26:52,650 --> 00:26:54,790
You don't have one showing his face?

364
00:26:54,790 --> 00:26:56,850
Look at the next one.

365
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:03,070
It's this man who wanted the package delivered to you.

366
00:27:03,070 --> 00:27:06,570
I don't think he intended to hide his face.

367
00:27:07,530 --> 00:27:09,810
Where did I see him?

368
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:14,120
   

369
00:27:17,490 --> 00:27:20,240
I told you not to buy this.

370
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,830
It's about time for your refills.

371
00:27:22,830 --> 00:27:24,770
Wait a minute.

372
00:27:24,770 --> 00:27:26,330
I'll give you the money.

373
00:27:26,330 --> 00:27:29,300
Wait, just count it even for the dry cleaning fee.

374
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:31,020
You don't even get things dry-cleaned. Here, take it.

375
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:33,320
No, that's too much.

376
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:35,630
Gosh, you bought so many for me already!

377
00:27:35,630 --> 00:27:39,140
Gosh, okay. I'll take it.

378
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,280
Is your knee pain better now?

379
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:44,100
Well, it's a chronic illness.

380
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:46,800
But taking the meds seems to improve it.

381
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:48,620
I'm glad.

382
00:27:50,220 --> 00:27:52,810
    
 Noh Myeong Nam is the one who sent me the novel.

383
00:27:52,810 --> 00:27:54,050
I'm sure of it.

384
00:27:54,050 --> 00:27:56,780
I checked his picture a few days ago while looking up his release date.

385
00:27:56,780 --> 00:27:59,140
And I checked it again just now.

386
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,760
Did you meet him?

387
