388
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,970
Thank you.

389
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:24,740
Jeon Doo Hyeon was murdered two years ago.

390
00:28:24,740 --> 00:28:26,540
You're aware. Right?

391
00:28:40,590 --> 00:28:44,010
   

392
00:28:55,690 --> 00:28:58,390
Noh Myeong Nam ran away. I'll send his license plate number.

393
00:28:58,390 --> 00:29:01,120
Issue a warrant on the car and track his phone.

394
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:02,610
Yes.

395
00:29:19,710 --> 00:29:21,480
Writer Yook!

396
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:24,540
Why won't you answer your phone?

397
00:29:24,540 --> 00:29:28,350
I'm sorry, but I have a bad headache right now.

398
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:31,110
I placed the bed just where you said you wanted it.

399
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:35,010
Oh, okay. Thank you. I'll send the bed cost to the publishing company's account.

400
00:29:35,010 --> 00:29:38,110
Please forget about it now. CEO Lee is resolving the issue regarding Director Shin's script—

401
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:40,860
- That's not even important. 
 - I understand how you feel—

402
00:29:40,860 --> 00:29:43,520
- N-No, no one can understand me! 
 - I do!

403
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:46,540
Plagiarism is taboo for writers.

404
00:29:46,540 --> 00:29:49,710
To be real, there's nothing new under the sun.

405
00:29:49,710 --> 00:29:52,710
Are all writers who came after Shakespeare plagiarizing him, then?

406
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:56,480
Can't we talk later? I have a huge headache right now.

407
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:59,260
I'm sure CEO Lee also had a headache.

408
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:02,760
Similar works do come out around the same time.

409
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:05,300
But they were indeed too similar.

410
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:09,610
So, what parts were that similar, and in what way specifically?

411
00:30:09,610 --> 00:30:13,990
They both take place at a lake, and the murders are described the same way.

412
00:30:13,990 --> 00:30:16,400
In the actual case, the culprit was caught. Right?

413
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,400
But the case was covered up in the novel.

414
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,370
The script has the same plot.

415
00:30:20,370 --> 00:30:24,350
The culprits are powerful families' kids in high school.

416
00:30:25,970 --> 00:30:29,870
Are you saying the circumstances of the murders are the same?

417
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:32,480
Surprisingly so.

418
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:36,200
But I'm not saying you plagiarized, so don't misunderstand me.

419
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:38,790
The stories progress completely differently in the latter part.

420
00:30:40,010 --> 00:30:45,310
By the way, did Director Shin graduate from Taekang High School?

421
00:30:46,060 --> 00:30:48,130
I think so.

422
00:30:48,130 --> 00:30:50,700
I think I read it in a magazine interview.

423
