430
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:48,830
   

431
00:31:54,010 --> 00:31:55,930
   

432
00:31:57,330 --> 00:31:59,010
 Kill him! 

433
00:31:59,740 --> 00:32:03,070
   

434
00:32:03,930 --> 00:32:05,340
 Let me! Let me! 

435
00:32:09,860 --> 00:32:13,350
   

436
00:32:14,650 --> 00:32:18,360
   

437
00:32:19,390 --> 00:32:20,920
 Die, you bastard! 

438
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:24,630
 Hell is empty... 

439
00:32:24,630 --> 00:32:28,250
 and all the demons are here. 

440
00:32:32,300 --> 00:32:36,930
   

441
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,720
Where'd he go?

442
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:27,500
Why won't it work?

443
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:43,160
- Excuse me? 
 - Yes?

444
00:33:44,910 --> 00:33:47,080
Why won't he pick up his phone?

445
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:50,670
Hey, Lee Kang San— I mean... Lee Gi Jeok! Where are you?

446
00:33:50,670 --> 00:33:52,320
 My last name is Lee? 

447
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:55,800
Lee or Kim, where are you?

448
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:58,590
Where are you going when you don't even know the way?

449
00:34:01,130 --> 00:34:04,570
I can just use my phone's navigation.

450
00:34:04,570 --> 00:34:08,190
I have plans. I need to meet someone.

451
00:34:08,190 --> 00:34:10,310
Who would you even meet?

452
00:34:10,310 --> 00:34:12,780
You think I have no one to meet?

453
00:34:12,780 --> 00:34:14,530
- Who is it? 
 - Someone.

454
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:16,930
- I asked who is it? 
 - None of your business.

455
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:18,300
That female student?

456
00:34:18,300 --> 00:34:19,840
It's not.

457
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:20,990
It is.

458
00:34:20,990 --> 00:34:23,300
I'll pay you back later.

459
00:34:34,150 --> 00:34:36,210
   

460
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,360
   

461
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,200
   

462
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:50,540
I must meet him before the police find him.

463
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:54,300
   

464
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:56,580
Dying is the worst that could happen.

465
00:35:00,100 --> 00:35:03,960
   

466
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:06,100
Gosh...

467
00:35:11,010 --> 00:35:12,050
   

468
00:35:12,050 --> 00:35:16,050
It's a photo of him from 27 years ago. He's currently 46 years old.

469
00:35:16,050 --> 00:35:18,690
We can obtain an age progression montage. Right?

470
00:35:18,690 --> 00:35:20,050
Who is this?

471
00:35:20,050 --> 00:35:22,480
I ask you this favor.

472
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,730
How could I say no when it's a favor for Detective Park?

473
00:35:24,730 --> 00:35:26,690
Thank you.

474
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,030
Yes.

475
00:35:34,030 --> 00:35:36,170
Noh Myeong Nam's phone is off.

476
00:35:36,170 --> 00:35:38,580
We found his car nearby.

477
00:35:39,530 --> 00:35:41,960
I'll head back for now. Let's talk then.

478
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:49,290
This is Park Hyeon Soo.

479
00:35:49,290 --> 00:35:51,300
 I didn't kill him. 

480
00:35:51,300 --> 00:35:55,120
Noh Myeong Nam? You're Noh Myeong Nam, aren't you?

481
00:35:55,120 --> 00:36:00,020
 I didn't kill him. I didn't kill anyone. 

482
00:36:00,020 --> 00:36:03,300
Let's meet and talk. I'll head over to where you are.

483
00:36:03,300 --> 00:36:05,640
I won't fall for it this time.

484
00:36:07,450 --> 00:36:08,730
I won't fall for it twice.

485
00:36:08,730 --> 00:36:10,670
I'll believe you. I believe you.

486
00:36:10,670 --> 00:36:14,110
So let's meet up. If you run away, you'll become a suspect—

487
00:36:16,770 --> 00:36:19,180
What the hell are you thinking?

488
00:36:19,180 --> 00:36:21,880
Why are you digging up a closed case instead of investigating what you're supposed to?

489
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:25,190
- Well... 
 - I'm getting pressured from above, my junior's fumbling around, and the press is talking shit.

490
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:29,860
I'm working my ass off! What are you doing by yourself? Aren't you Violent Crimes Team 3?

491
00:36:29,860 --> 00:36:32,550
You think you're all that? You need to share information!

492
00:36:32,550 --> 00:36:34,000
I was going to tell you.

493
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:35,990
When? After I'm dead?

494
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:37,850
The Sopyeong Lake incident from 27 years ago

495
00:36:37,850 --> 00:36:41,160
is the motive behind the Shin Kyeong Cheol/Jeon Doo Hyeon case.

496
00:36:42,950 --> 00:36:45,090
What do you mean? Explain so I can understand.

497
00:36:45,090 --> 00:36:46,890
Let me explain.

498
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:51,900
The case from 27 years ago was covered up

499
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:54,280
and it was the motive for Shin Kyeong Cheol/Jeon Doo Hyeon's murder case?

500
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:59,520
Yes. The culprits are in the photo found in Jeon Doo Hyeon's pocket, Chairman Lee Tae Man and—

501
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:01,500
Hey, get out.

502
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:04,680
- Team Leader Oh... 
 - Didn't you hear what I said?

503
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:09,230
Okay.

504
00:37:17,770 --> 00:37:21,850
Hyungnim, you know what you're implying, don't you?

505
00:37:21,850 --> 00:37:25,920
Byeon Jong Il, an incumbent lawmaker and former detective,

506
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:31,610
was encouraged by powerful elites to cover up the case.

507
00:37:31,610 --> 00:37:33,900
And I'm also an accomplice.

508
00:37:35,580 --> 00:37:39,720
What's gotten into you? You shouldn't do this without any evidence.

509
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:43,630
I was in charge of this case. Aside from everything else,

510
00:37:43,630 --> 00:37:47,280
it's highly likely that Noh Myeong Nam isn't the culprit of the case from 27 years ago.

511
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,780
Wait a minute.

512
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:53,190
So Noh Myeong Nam is the one who killed Shin Kyeong Cheol and Jeon Doo Hyeon?

513
00:37:53,190 --> 00:37:58,540
Based on the call Detective Park received from Noh Myeong Nam, we don't think he's the culprit.

514
00:37:58,540 --> 00:38:01,190
You said he ran away. Why would he run if he's innocent?

515
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:02,730
I'm not sure.

516
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:08,650
In any case, I'm certain the case from 27 years ago is the key to solving this one.

517
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:20,110
Whether it's true or not, you know what will happen if this story gets out.

518
00:38:20,110 --> 00:38:22,590
The entire police force will be criticized.

519
00:38:22,590 --> 00:38:28,110
Some higher-ups will be stripped of their uniforms. Including me.

520
00:38:28,110 --> 00:38:31,480
You might be stripped before you even start to investigate.

521
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:34,080
Hyungnim,

522
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:39,470
let's bury the case with the expired statute of limitations and just catch the culprit for this case.

523
00:38:40,500 --> 00:38:43,180
If we want to catch this culprit, we need to dig up the past.

524
00:38:43,180 --> 00:38:46,310
